Sure, here's an example Python code using the `pandas` library to read data from a spreadsheet (e.g. Excel or CSV file):

```
import pandas as pd

def read_spreadsheet(filename):
    # Load spreadsheet into a DataFrame object
    df = pd.read_csv(filename)
    
    return df
```

You can call this function by passing the filename of your spreadsheet to it, and it will return a `DataFrame` object containing all the data from the spreadsheet.
